Run the Dockerized Postgres (DEV)

Prerequisites:
- Docker installed on your machine.
- Docker Compose installed on your machine.

Start:
#From the directory containing the docker-compose.yml file, run:
docker-compose up -d
#This command will start the PostgreSQL server in detached mode.

docker compose ps
#This command will show the running containers.

docker compose logs -f db
#This command will show the logs of the PostgreSQL container.

